📘 What is grep?
grep is a powerful Linux utility used to search for specific patterns in text files.
It's especially useful when working with large files or log data.

🧾 General Syntax
bash
Copy
Edit
grep [OPTIONS] 'search_pattern' filename
Wrap the search pattern in single quotes to avoid issues with special characters (e.g., *, ?).

🔎 Basic Search Example
bash
Copy
Edit
grep 'password' /etc/ssh/sshd_config
Case-sensitive → only matches lowercase "password"

bash
Copy
Edit
grep 'Password' /etc/ssh/sshd_config
Matches "Password" with uppercase P

🔁 Case-Insensitive Search
Use the -i option:

bash
Copy
Edit
grep -i 'password' /etc/ssh/sshd_config
Matches both "password", "Password", etc.

📂 Recursive Search (Directory & Subdirectories)
Use the -r (recursive) option:

bash
Copy
Edit
grep -r -i 'password' /etc/
Searches all files under /etc/ recursively, case-insensitive.

🚫 Handling Permission Denied
Some files may return "Permission Denied" unless using sudo:

bash
Copy
Edit
sudo grep -r -i 'password' /etc/
🎨 Enable Colored Output (Force Color)
sudo may remove color output. Use:

bash
Copy
Edit
sudo grep --color -r -i 'password' /etc/
🔄 Invert Match (Show lines NOT containing pattern)
Use the -v (invert) option:

bash
Copy
Edit
grep -v 'password' /etc/ssh/sshd_config
🧩 Match Whole Word Only
Use -w (word match):

bash
Copy
Edit
grep -w 'password' /etc/ssh/sshd_config
Will not match "passwords", only the word "password".

🔍 Example:
passwordAuthentication will not match because it's a different word for grep.

📤 Show Only the Matched Part (No Context)
Use -o (only matching):

bash
Copy
Edit
grep -o 'password' /etc/ssh/sshd_config
Outputs only the exact matching word instead of the whole line.

🔧 Useful for:

Scripting

Data extraction

Filtering specific values

✅ Summary Table
Task	Command
Basic search	grep 'word' file.txt
Case-insensitive	grep -i 'word' file.txt
Recursive search	grep -r 'word' /path/
Ignore case + recursive	grep -r -i 'word' /path/
With root access	sudo grep 'word' file.txt
Force color output	--color
Exclude matches	-v
Match whole word only	-w
Only matched text	-o